            "equations": [],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "polar_default_distribution",
                    "description": "All parameters at their declared defaults — the Polar size distribution of Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Table 8.3 (three lognormal modes: N = [21.7, 0.186, 3.0e-4] cm^-3, D_g = [0.138, 0.75, 8.6] um, log10 sigma = [0.245, 0.300, 0.291]; mode 1 an accumulation mode, modes 2-3 coarse modes), evaluated at D_p = 1.0e-7 m (0.1 um). Pins every one of the ten outputs: the number/surface/volume distribution densities n_N_o/n_S_o/n_V_o (Eq. 8.54/8.49/8.52), the total concentrations N_t/S_t/V_t, the mode-1 Hatch-Choate diameters D_s/D_v/D_bar, and the surface vertical mass ratio M_z. N_t = N_1+N_2+N_3 = (21.7+0.186+3.0e-4)e6 = 2.18863e7 m^-3; M_z = exp(-z/H_p) = 1 at the surface (z = 0). All outputs are algebraic and time-independent, so N_t and M_z are also asserted at t = 1 to confirm time-invariance.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "n_N_o",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 30024221.008973014
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "n_S_o",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.782649570590063e-06
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "n_V_o",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 6.583858264706595e-14
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "N_t",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 21886300.0
                        },
                        {
